<HEADLINE> Satellite Launch Delayed Due to Weather Conditions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XICHANG, August 17 (Xinhua) -- A commercial satellite launch
scheduled for the early hours of August 18 was delayed due to
unsuitable weather conditions in Xichang, the launching center in
southwest China's Sichuan Province, according to sources.
</P>
<P>
The telecommunication satellite, made by US-based Space
Systems/Loral Inc. (SS/L) for the Mabuhay Philippines Satellite
Corporation (MPSC), will be sent into space by the China-made Long
March 3b rocket.
</P>
<P>
Sources in charge of the launch said that everything, including
the satellite, rocket and ground facilities, is "ready for the
launching."
</P>
<P>
"Once weather permitted, the satellite will be sent off
immediately," one source said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
