<HEADLINE> Palestinian Prisoners on Hunger Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian prisoners in
Israeli jails today staged a one-day hunger strike to protest
against maltreatment.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian political prisoners in the Israeli Nafha Jail in
Negev Desert first started the strike to plead the improvement of
living conditions in prison.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement issued by the the Palestinian
Prisoners' Committee, the Palestinian prisoners in Nafha Jail
demanded halting the use of tear gas against their cells,
supplying adequate good food and medical treatment, transferring
political prisoners from departments of criminals.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that Palestinian prisoners in other Israeli
jails showed today their solidarity with the Nafha's inmates by
participating in the hunger strike.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile the Palestinian Prisoner's Club called the
international community to bear its responsibilities towards
ending the sufferings of the Palestinian prisoners in Israeli
jails. 
</P>
</TEXT>
