<HEADLINE> Kuwait Reiterates Ban on Prohibited Foreign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait today vowed to try
every means to keep out prohibited foreign products, including
those carried by its citizens returning from vacations overseas.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of Kuwaitis and foreign employees usually leave
Kuwait on vocation this time of the year every year to get away
from the world's hottest summer there.
</P>
<P>
Director General of Customs Department Ibrahim Abdulla
Al-Ghanim said in a statement to official Kuwait News Agency that
his administration has taken all the necessary precautions and
procedures to avoid the entrance to the country of any prohibited
products.
</P>
<P>
The official specified two lists of all the prohibited
products. One includes 47 items while the other 62 items.
</P>
<P>
The prohibited products include some specified food, drinks,
electrical appliances, firecrackers, military uniforms, mobile
phones exceeding 300 milliwatts, drugs, alcohol and weapons.
</P>
<P>
Other prohibited items to the country include African birds,
Iraqi money, gas cylinders of all sizes as well as obscene
products which offend religion, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that some of the items prohibited to be
brought into the country personally may be imported by organized
activities in cooperation with governmental authorities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
