<HEADLINE> Cantona to Settle Dispute with United </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Former Manchester United striker
Eric Cantona will have his lawyers meet his former club officials
later Monday to discuss the United's illegal use of his name for
marketing profits.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that Cantona will claim for a total of 750,000
pounds pay-off, which is part of the money the club has made on
replica shirts bearing his name.
</P>
<P>
United's chief executive Martin Edwards admitted that "Eric
wants some money from us" but he denied that Cantona has started
legal action against the club .
</P>
<P>
"There are discussions going on between us and Eric's lawyer
Jean-Jacques Bertrand. Eric has not issued a writ," said Edwards.
</P>
<P>
The United agreed that not market Eric Cantona products from
July 31. The Frenchman retired in May after being a household star
in Manchester for six seasons.
</P>
<P>
Cantona has already taken legal steps to register a copyright
on the words "Ooh Aah Cantona" and "Cantona 7". 
</P>
