<HEADLINE> China Develops Color Liquid Crystal Displays </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, August 18 (Xinhua) -- China has become the third
country in the world capable of producing color liquid crystal
display (LCD) systems, following Japan and the United States.
</P>
<P>
The country's first LCD manufacture company today broke ground
in northeast China's Dalian city.
</P>
<P>
According to sources, the Dalian Dongfang Computer Holding
Company (Dongfang) developed China's first color LCD after three
years of research and development.
</P>
<P>
At a cost of 31 million US dollars, the new Dalian Dongfu Color
LCD Co. Ltd. was jointly funded by Dongfang, Dalian Development
Zone Development Corporation and a Taiwan company.
</P>
<P>
The designed capacity of the venture is one million 10.4-inch
LCDs, 80 percent of which are for export.
</P>
<P>
The products can be widely applied to notebook computers, video
telephones, large TV screens and other display devices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
