<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines' Exports to ASEAN Jump </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' exports to its
Southeast Asian neighbors reached 1.4 billion U.S. dollars in the
first semester this year, a 25-percent surge over the same period
last year, official figures showed today.
</P>
<P>
The country's exports to ASEAN members accounted for 14.8
percent of its total exports during the period, a slight increase
from the 14.5 percent recorded last year, according to the data
released by the Department of Trade and Industry.
</P>
<P>
Of its eight ASEAN neighbors, Singapore was the largest buyer
of the Philippine products, with its import payments rising by 23
percent to 626.5 million dollars for the period.
</P>
<P>
Thailand came second buying 404 million dollars worth of the
Philippine products, up by 21 percent from a year ago.
</P>
<P>
The country's top export markets continued to be the United
States and Japan, which accounted for over half of its exports for
the first five months.
</P>
<P>
The nine-member ASEAN also groups Vietnam, Malaysia, Indonesia,
Laos, Maynmar and Brunei.  
</P>
</TEXT>
