<HEADLINE> Italian Basketball Player Collapses in Action </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Italian basketball player Davide
Ancilotto collapsed during a tournament match and was rushed to
hospital here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ancilotto remained unconscious for 90 minutes. Initial tests
showed no brain damage but a medical bulletin on Sunday said: "The
patient is in a coma, and remains in a serious condition."
</P>
<P>
Doctors at Rome's San Filippo Neri hospital on Monday had
wanted to carry out a more extensive detailed brain scan using
magnetic resonance technology -- but the player's condition was
judged too perilous.
</P>
<P>
Hospital sources quoted by ANSA news agency said the player's
chances of survival were now slim and that the hours ahead on
Monday would be decisive.
</P>
<P>
Doctors were speculating that Ancilotti may have suffered a
brain haemorrhage or a loss of blood supply to the brain during
the match, which was played between Telemarket and French side
Nancy at Gubbio, near Perugia in central Italy. 
</P>
