<HEADLINE> Mine Explosion in Burundi Kills 10 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Ten civilians were killed when
a mini-bus set off an anti-tank mine on a road south of Bujumbura,
a report from the Burundi capital said today.
</P>
<P>
An official of the Burundi Defense Ministry was quoted as
saying today that "a mini-bus rolled over an anti-tank mine on
national route 3. We don't know exactly how many were injured,
but the mine was laid by rebels."
</P>
<P>
The mini-bus was carrying passengers through Muhuta commune,
30 kilometers south of the capital. On August 4, four civilians
were killed when a bus hit a mine on the same route.
</P>
<P>
Also on August 4, nine more people were killed and nine
wounded when their bus detonated a mine on its way to Bujumbura
from northwestern Cibitoke province, Burundi radio said.
</P>
<P>
Over 150,000 people have died in killings during civil
conflicts between the Tutsi-dominated army and Hutu rebels since
the assassination of Burundi's first Hutu president Melchior
Ndadaye on October 21, 1993. 
</P>
