<DOCNO> XIE19970818.0057 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Successful Macro-Control A Prelude for Further Development (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Editor's note: To welcome the
15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China, Xinhua
News Agency will from today on issue a series of articles on
China's reform and development based on interviews with
ministers. The following is the first story in the sequence.
</P>
<P>
China's macro-economic control drive in the past four years is
responsible for the country's swift economic growth in tandem with
effectively curbed inflation, and has laid a solid foundation for
economic and social trans-century development, said Chinese State
Planning Minister Chen Jinhua.
</P>
<P>
"The success of the macro-economic control drive is a good
indication that the Chinese government has learned a great deal
about the law of the socialist market economy, and increased its
ability to control a macro-economy and deal with economic
difficulties," Chen said in an interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
China started its macro-economic control effort in June, 1993,
in face of an overheated economy and double-digit inflation. But
the retail price index was brought down to 1.8 percent for the
first half of this year, while the economy kept growing at 9.5
percent.
</P>
<P>
Both domestic and overseas experience has shown that sharp
reductions in inflation usually result in an ever-changing and
volatile economy, said Chen.
</P>
<P>
The crowning success of the macro-economic control drive was
that China realized effective inflation control accompanied by a
moderately fast growth in economy, the minister added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970818.0058 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Successful Macro-Control A Prelude for Further Development (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chen attributed the accomplishment to well-chosen macro-control
policies, a greater variety of macro-control means, as well as
proper timing and flexibility of the policies.
</P>
<P>
As for demand, the Chinese government has imposed strict
measures to check the fixed-asset investment scale through a
moderately tight fiscal and money policy.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the growth in fixed-asset investment slowed down
to 12 percent during the January-June period from the 58.6 percent
in 1992, and the money supply also decreased gradually.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the central government also sought to increase
supply by attaching greater importance to the agriculture,
infrastructure facilities and basic industries, which led to a
progressive balance of supply and demand in the national economy.
</P>
<P>
The nation twice lifted purchasing price for grains in the past
four years and increased funding for agriculture, thereby boosting
the farmers' interest in farming, which in turn resulted in bumper
crops. Ultimately, the price hike in farm and non-staple products
which was once a leading contributor to the runaway inflation rate
was effectively restrained.
</P>
<P>
The shortage of some major production materials was turned
around, since top priority also went to industries in energy,
transportation, and raw materials.
</P>
<P>
Chen Jinhua pointed out that a salient feature of the
macro-control drive is that market-oriented economic leverages of
price, tax, credit, interest rate, and exchange rate played a
major role, instead of administrative and legal means.
</P>
<P>
"Our macro-control policies were drafted in line with the law
of value, and we also adopted both market-oriented and
administrative means to allocate the social resources. This is an
important reason behind the success of the macro-control drive,"
Chen stressed.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970818.0059 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Successful Macro-Control A Prelude for Further Development (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chinese government also made minor adjustments to the
macro-economic control policies over the past four years, based on
analysis and prediction of the national economy, while adhering to
a moderately tight fiscal and monetary policy, Chen noted.
</P>
<P>
To manage the high demand for capital, China raised the
interest rates of bank borrowings and lendings, and the relending
rate of the central bank on four occasions.
</P>
<P>
And when the inflation pressure eased, the government
authorized two rounds of cuts in the interest rates of bank
deposits and loans to lighten the loan burden on the businesses
and boost their production.
</P>
<P>
Chen also pointed out that the success of macro-economic
control is inseparable from the deepening of the economic reform.
</P>
<P>
In 1994, China successfully reformed its fiscal and tax
systems, system of finance, foreign exchange, investment and
circulation, which led to a more workable implementation of the
macro-control policies and offered solutions for deep-rooted
problems in the national economy, explained the minister.
</P>
<P>
Chen Jinhua said he believed that the macro-economic control
drive in the past four years has been a successful practice under
the socialist market economy and will provide "invaluable
experience" for putting the Chinese economy on a sound development
course.
</P>
<P>
He also pledged that reform would be deepened in the
state-owned enterprises and the economic structure would be
further adjusted to guarantee the healthy development of the
overall economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970818.0060 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-18 </DATE_TIME>
