<HEADLINE> East China on Alert for Strong Typhoon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 18 (Xinhua) -- People and flood control units
in east China's Zhejiang Province and Shanghai Municipality are
well-braced for a powerful typhoon which may hit the region
tonight.
</P>
<P>
Weather forecasters have predicted that typhoon "Number 11," or
Typhoon Winnie as it was called before it lands at Zhejiang's
coasts between Shipu and Pingyang around midnight, along with
thunderstorms and tidal waves, will hit coastal region of the
Province, then move eastward or northward, where it will affect
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Municipal Government has required all departments
concerned to prepare for the imminent typhoon. The municipality's
street lights and billboards have been inspected and reinforced,
and residents have moved flower vases inside from their balconies.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang provincial authorities have further reinforced the
Qiantang Dyke to resist and combat the strong tides expected to
occur at the same time as the typhoon. All ships, including more
than 5,000 vessels from Taiwan, were called back to safe harbors.
</P>
<P>
The People's Liberation Armymen and Armed Police units
stationed there have also been put on alert.  
</P>
