for Friendship with Foreign Countries gave a reception here today
to mark the 5th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic
relations between China and the Republic of Korea (ROK).
</P>
<P>
Addressing the reception, Qi Huaiyuan, president of the host
association, said that China and ROK are close neighbors, whose
peoples enjoy traditional friendship.
</P>
<P>
Since the forging of diplomatic links in 1992, he said, the two
countries have achieved great development in bilateral exchanges
and cooperation in the fields of politics, economics, culture,
science and technology.
</P>
<P>
The development of Sino-ROK friendly relations is not only in
the fundamental interests of the two peoples but also beneficial
to the stability and prosperity in the Korean Peninsula as well as
to the peace and development in the Asia-Pacific region and the
world as a whole, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Among those present at the reception were Tomur Dawamat,
vice-chairman of China's National People's Congress Standing
Committee; Tang Jiaxuan, Chinese vice-foreign minister; Zhu Muzhi,
president of China-ROK Friendship Association; and Chong Wook
Chung, ambassador of ROK to China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
