<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Weaker In A Narrow Range </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar today
ended weaker against the U.S. dollar after spending much of the
session trading in a narrow range, also sidelined by action in the
local stock market.
</P>
<P>
The currency ended at 74.26 U.S. cents, down from 74.34
previously.
</P>
<P>
"There is no real enthusiasm out there, but there is some short
term buying," said Rothschild Australia senior foreign exchange
trader Paul Macarounas.
</P>
<P>
A few participants think the Reserve Bank of Australia could
cut official interest rates again before year-end. Tomorrow the
Reserve Bank will release its August bulletin that will contain
its quarterly report on the economy and financial markets.
</P>
<P>
"No doubt the bulletin is likely to maintain the upbeat tenor
on the inflation outlook already alluded to in the governors'
speech," Hambros economist Su-Lin Ong said.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar ended at 87.00 from 87.95 late Friday
against yen and it was at 1.3458 down from 1.3707 against mark.
 
