<HEADLINE> Army Bomb Squad Defuses Explosives Found in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 18 (Xinhua) -- An army bomb disposal squad
Sunday defused a hand grenade and a bomb which were found hidden
in an abandoned well near Anurdhapura city in North-Central
Province of Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
According to police sources here today, the hand grenade and
the bomb were discovered by workers when they cleaned the well.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary investigation ruled out any Tamil rebel
involvement, but the sources said that the explosives may be
dumped in the well by an errant soldier or policemen, who
originally have wanted to sell them to the underworld or for some
personal purpose, but later got cold feet and feared to be
discovered, the sources added.  
</P>
