<HEADLINE> Share Prices Decline Sharply on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined on the
Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index
fell sharply by 34.95 points to close at 1,918.85 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume stood at 170.16 million units, valued
at 562.92 million Singapore dollars (about 372.79 million US
dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 324 to 36, while 248
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Local hotel group Amara was the most actively traded stock as
it registered a turnover of 22.2 million units. It was followed by
Hotung which had 12.48 million shares traded. The Hong Kong Land
was next with 8.78 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign led the gainers of
the day as it rose by one dollar to finish at 23 Singapore
dollars. The Development Bank of Singapore (DBS) Foreign gained 90
cents to end at 16.7 Singapore dollars and the United Overseas
Bank (UOB) Foreign increased by 80 cents to close at 13.1
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Malaya Banking was the biggest loser as it
declined by 1.5 dollars to end at 11 Singapore dollars. Jardine
Matheson Holdings fell by 90 cents to close at 6.75 US dollars,
while DBS finished 65 cents lower at 9.75 Singapore dollars.
</P>
