<HEADLINE> CCD Committee to Prepare for First Ministerial Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The Intergovernmental Negotiating
Committee for the Convention to Combat Desertification (CCD)
begins a five-day session, the 10th of the kind, here today.
</P>
<P>
The meeting aims at finalizing arrangements for the first
ministerial Conference of the Parties (COP) of the CCD scheduled
for September 29 through October 10 in Rome, said a press release
by the CCD interim secretariat currently based in Geneva.
</P>
<P>
The COP conference is expected to choose the site of the
convention's permanent secretariat among the three cities -- Bonn,
Montreal and Murcia.
</P>
<P>
The Intergovernmental Negotiating Committee will consider a
number of issues this week, including the identity of the
organization to house the "Global Mechanism" for mobilizing
financial resources. It may also discuss the revised offers of the
International Fund for Agricultural Development (IFAD) and the
United Nations Development Program (UNDP).
</P>
<P>
What is "of special concern" at the COP ministerial conference,
the interim secretariat said, is the organization of a discussion
on steps that have been taken to implement the resolution on
urgent action for Africa, and on initiatives taken in the Asian,
Latin American and Caribbean, and Northern Mediterranean regions.
</P>
<P>
Other issues will be the secretariat's program and budget for
1998/99 and the Rules of Procedure for the COP. 
</P>
</TEXT>
