detected in Vietnam and 882 of them have developed into full-blown
aids so far.
</P>
<P>
By August 11, 478 AIDS-related deaths have been reported, said
the report.
</P>
<P>
Ho Chi Minh City topped on the list of HIV/AIDS cases with
2,311 patients of the disease.
</P>
<P>
Vietnamese Deputy Prime Minister Nguyen Khanh met the National
HIV/AIDS Committee Saturday and discussed how to boost the
detection and control of the disease.
</P>
<P>
He asked the committee to make greater efforts in detecting
HIV/AIDS cases and preventing the disease from spreading. 
