<HEADLINE> Meeting Focuses on Africa's Genetic Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 18 (Xinhua) -- A symposium on natural
products starts here today to discuss genetic resources in the
continent.
</P>
<P>
The five-day symposium is organized by the Natural Products
Research Network for Eastern and Central Africa (NAPRECA).
</P>
<P>
A NAPRECA newsletter said that the symposium is to focus on
"research and development in utilization of Africa's genetic
resources for the pharmaceutical and agricultural industries
involving botany, pharmacology and environment".
</P>
<P>
The objectives of the symposium are to bring together and
foster interaction among scientists involved in
multi-disciplinary research in natural products.
</P>
<P>
Most of the participants to the symposium are researchers on
natural products from Cameroun, Madagascar, Ethiopia, Kenya,
Sudan, Botswana, Uganda, South Africa, Tanzania, India, Portugal
and Canada.
</P>
<P>
There are also participants from Zimbabwe, Switzerland, the
United Kingdom, Germany, the United States, and Denmark. 
</P>
</TEXT>
