<HEADLINE> Hangzhou Land Administrative Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Hangzhou, a famous scenic city
and the capital of east China's Zhejiang Province, has set up a
special committee to administer land purchases and reserves.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, the committee is in charge of
protecting farmland from further shrinkage, ensuring the rational
use of available land in urban areas, standardizing and unifying
land deals, and optimizing land distribution.
</P>
<P>
The committee will also formulate policies related to land
purchases, reserves and transfers, and will draw up plans for all
related activities.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the committee will manage a land reserve
development center that will operate state-owned land assets.
</P>
<P>
Hangzhou has also stipulated that all land plots available for
trade or purchase will initially be held in reserve by the center
which will then transfer land to different units in accordance
with state industrial development policies.
</P>
<P>
The city has also established a land reserve fund of 20 million
yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
