<HEADLINE> Uganda to Build Power Dam on Nile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Uganda has decided to start
building a dam for power plant on Nile in June 1998, reported the
local daily, The Monitor, today.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the plant, called Nile Independent Power
Dam in Mukono district about 30 kilometers east of Kampala, will
last about four years.
</P>
<P>
George Kihuguru, official of the project was quoted as saying
that the dam, with a designed capacity of 290 megawatts when
completed, is far above the 180 megawatts being produced by the
state-owned Uganda Electricity Board at present.
</P>
<P>
According to the paper, the 450-million-U.S.-Dollar power
project is a joint venture between an Indian group and an
America-based firm.
</P>
<P>
Nitin Madhvani, representative of the Indian group was quoted
as saying that the project shall avail an opportunity of about
5,000 jobs both at the time of construction and after.
</P>
<P>
Over 184 families displaced as a result of flooding during
construction have been guaranteed to be compensated, the paper
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
