<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Desertification Control in Xinjiang Fruitful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, August 18 (Xinhua) -- While many parts of the world are
confronted with encroaching deserts, the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region in northwest China has transformed some 13,000 ha of desert
into oases in each of the past nine years.
</P>
<P>
The massive reclamation effort has been carried out by the
Xinjiang Production and Construction Corp, the largest state farm
in China with a work force of 2.3 million.
</P>
<P>
The corp, which has led the country in land reclamation and
desert control in recent years, has invested 1.29 billion yuan in
reclaiming 126,000 ha of barren land and improving 171,600 ha of
low-yield field.
</P>
<P>
Comprehensive agricultural development has helped to transform
Xinjiang's vast wilderness ares into forests and arable land. As a
result, the corps has produced an extra 93,000 tons of cotton and
512,000 tons of sugar beets so far. 
</P>
</TEXT>
