<HEADLINE> Booming Private Auto Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Today's edition of "People's
Daily" reports that more Chinese citizens are purchasing private
cars.
</P>
<P>
The Automobile Trade Market in Beijing's Asian Games Village
sold 9,843 cars valued at 1.3 billion yuan during the first
four months of this year, with 7,685 private cars accounting for
81 percent of total sales.
</P>
<P>
A recent urban survey revealed that 64.2 percent of respondents
favored the private car ownership.
</P>
<P>
Respondents also indicated they would rather spend 400,000 yuan
buying a luxury apartment in the suburbs and a car rather than buy
a luxury apartment in a downtown area.
</P>
<P>
The vast demand for private cars should be guided and
specialized automobile markets should be built, in a bid to
revitalize and develop China's auto industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
