<HEADLINE> 50 Army Deserters Arrested In Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan police have arrested
about 50 army deserters in Central Province and handed them over
to army centers recently, according to reports reaching here
today.
</P>
<P>
The deserters were arrested on the order of the Ministry of
Defense and local police are making further attempts to arrest
others who are hiding in the area, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
More than 20,000 has reportedly deserted the army in recent
years. Since 1995, the army has offered amnesty for deserters on
five occasions and over 10,000 deserters have reportedly returned.
</P>
<P>
During the latest amnesty on July 10-26 this year, a total of
4,206 army deserters returned for duty.  
</P>
