<HEADLINE> Stability, New Serbian Government's Top Priority: Lilic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Serbia's presidential candidate
Zoran Lilic said today that the top priority for a new government
and president of Serbia is to maintain stability in the republic
and enhance the living standards of its people, the Tanjug news
agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the USA Today newspaper, Lilic noted that, if
elected, he would stick to a policy of keeping Serbia united.
</P>
<P>
He also detailed the political and economic situation in Serbia
to the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Lilic, former president of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia,
was replaced by former Serbian president Slobodan Milosevic last
month.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Republic of Yugoslavia is composed of the Republic
of Serbia and the Republic of Montenegro.
</P>
<P>
Serbia's presidential and parliamentary elections are scheduled
for September 21. 
