<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beach Landslide Kills One, Injures Two in Bulgaria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, August 17 (Xinhua) -- A landslide by the Black Sea in
northern Bulgaria killed one and injured two today, the Bulgarska
Telegrafna Agentsia reported.
</P>
<P>
The landslide occurred this noon near a beach called "the
Shepherd", somewhere between Albena and Belchik, burying people
in sand and mud.
</P>
<P>
A baby less than three years old was evacuated together with
his parents from the mud, but died halfway to the hospital. No
more people were found beneath the mud.
</P>
<P>
The landslide is over 10-meter long, 20 to 25-meter wide and
3-meter high. The collapsed area being small, the Bulgarian Navy
had to launch the rescue work from the sea.
</P>
<P>
Today's landslide is seen by experts as a continuation of Black
Sea seashore landslides in the north of the country, which started
at the beginning of this year and destroyed tens of villas and
some roads. 
</P>
</TEXT>
