<HEADLINE> Akatiev Wins 25km for Russia at European Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Alexei Akatiev of Russia wrapped
up the victory of the men's 25 kilometers open water race for
Russia at the European Swimming Championships in Seville, Spain on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Akatiev, who won the five-kilometer crown on Friday, swam ahead
of his rivals by more than three minutes and 30 seconds in the
River Guadalquivir.
</P>
<P>
The Russian was clocked five hours and five minutes while
Stephane Lecat of France and defending champion Christoph
Wandratsch of Germany touched home together and shared silver
medals.
</P>
<P>
Peggy Buechse of Germany won the women's five kilometer event
which was the last of the long-distance races in Seville.
</P>
<P>
Buechse was timed one hour and 51 minutes, edging Valeria
Casprini of Italy to the second with just one second behind.
</P>
</TEXT>
