<HEADLINE> Italy Name Bertolucci as Davis Cup Captain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Italy named Paolo Bertolucci as
their new Davis Cup tennis captain on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Bertolucci, a three-time Davis Cup finalist, takes over from
Adriano Panatta, who resigned late last month after a contractual
row with Paolo Galgani, president of the Italian Tennis Federation.
</P>
<P>
The 46-year-old Bertolucci will captain the Italians in their
Davis Cup semifinal against Sweden on September 19-21, a reward
for their shock 4-1 defeat of Spain in the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
The winners will meet either Australia or the United States in
the final. 
</P>
