<HEADLINE> China Newspaper Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The following are highlights of
major Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The frontpage of the leading national newspaper carried an
analytical article featuring great achievements that have been
scored in promoting ethical and cultural progress throughout the
country over the past month.
</P>
<P>
As part of the national drive to nurture fine social morals,
taxi drivers in Nanning, capital city of south China's Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region, have become even more polite and honest
toward passengers.
</P>
<P>
-- Construction of the Dachaoshan Power Station with a designed
capacity of 1.35 million kw in southwest China's Yunnan Province,
the second largest hydroelectric power station on the Lancang
River, has been approved by the central government.
</P>
<P>
-- Coastal areas in eastern China have explored some successful
ways of optimizing the use of labor resources and carry out the
reemployment program in the course of shifting from a planned
economy to a socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
-- The rural economy in central China's Hunan Province
continued to boom in the first half of the year. The added value
of agriculture rose by 7.5 percent over the same period last year,
and the total output value of township enterprises surged by 49.5
percent.
</P>
<P>
"Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- China has scored remarkable progress in preserving soil.
Over the past five years, a total of 177,000 sq km of land which
used to suffer from heavy soil erosion has been brought under
control.
</P>
<P>
-- Since the 14th National Congress of the Communist Party of
China in 1992, China's rural economy has been booming, with
steadily growing farm produces and township enterprises, higher
incomes of rural residents and better infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
-- A sample survey conducted by the State Statistics Bureau
shows that the cash income of Chinese farmers in the first half of
the year increased 3.3 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China's transport authorities are taking a close look at the
inferior level of maintenance of the country's fast-growing
highway network.
</P>
<P>
-- The first flame of the Eighth National Games was lit in
front of the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center, where the
handover ceremony of Hong Kong's return to the motherland was
held, Saturday morning in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
-- Seven Hong Kongers were confirmed dead Sunday after the
bodies of three passengers of a capsized pleasure boat in the
Philippines' Manila Bay were recovered on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
-- US National Security Adviser Samuel Berger said Saturday
that it is extremely important for the US to have regular
high-level talks with Chinese leaders. 
</P>
</TEXT>
