<HEADLINE> One Injured, Many Detained During Strike in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 18 (Xinhua) -- One person was injured and 59
were detained Sunday during a strike which swept Kathmandu,
Bhaktapur and Lalitpur, the three cities in the Kathmandu Valley.
</P>
<P>
The glasses of a number of vehicles were broken by the
protesters during the strike called by the Nepal Workers and
Peasants Party and several other small parties to protest against
terrorism, price hikes and crimes, said a spokesman for the Nepali
Home Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Few vehicles were seen on the roads except some motorbikes and
taxis, and most shops closed, affecting normal life in the valley.
</P>
<P>
Those taken into custody for blocking the traffic were released
after investigation on Sunday, the spokesman said.  
</P>
