<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian, British Police Seize Heroin in Siberia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Russian and British police have
seized 200 kilograms of heroin in Bratsk of Russian Siberia and
arrested seven drug-smugglers, according to local reports today.
</P>
<P>
This is the largest amount of heroin found in the drug market
of Siberia.
</P>
<P>
British customs officials discovered the drugs in a consignment
of South-America-made cans of pineapple being shipped from Britain
to Siberia. Russian and British police followed the cargo from
St. Petersburg to Bratsk and seized the drugs and arrested the
dealers.
</P>
<P>
Russia and Britain reached a protocol on fighting against
organized crimes in July when British Secretary of State for
Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs Robin Cook visited Russia. The
agreement will be signed at the end of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
