<DOCNO> XIE19970818.0155 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Authorities Warn Inadequate Road Repair Effort </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 18 (Xinhua) -- China's transport authorities
are taking a close look at the inferior level of maintenance of
the country's fast-growing highway network, today's China Daily
reported.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Communications has ordered practical measures
to be taken by localities to better road maintenance and
management to improve the condition of the highway transport
network throughout China and increase its efficiency, the English
newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
After an unprecedented highway construction boom in the past
decade, the total length of roads in the country now exceeds 1.18
million kilometers, and road travel has accounted for 88.7 percent
of the country's passenger transport volume and 91 percent of its
cargo transport.
</P>
<P>
However, road maintenance has been seriously neglected, as the
appetite for new road construction in localities has hampered the
healthy development of highways, the Daily quoted an official of
the ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
Every year 25,000 kilometers of new roads are added to the
network and these all require maintenance.
</P>
<P>
Traffic on half of the national highways has exceeded the
designed handling capacity.
</P>
<P>
Many of the highways are of low standard and susceptible to
natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
About 100,000 kilometers of the national and provincial
highways have extended their designated service life and need to
be renovated.
</P>
<P>
However, the limited funds from road maintenance raised from
each vehicle can scarcely make ends meet, the official noted.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the country's technological level in road repairs
is low and most of the repair work has been done by hand,
hindering efficiency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
