<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Stock Prices Fall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 18 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Stock Exchange
recorded slow trading and falling prices last week.
</P>
<P>
The Composite Stock Index fell 5.2 percent from the previous
week to 1,143.06 last week, with a weekly turnover of 19.537
billion yuan, roughly matching last week's figure. The blue chip
SSE-30 stock index dropped 6.3 percent to close at 3,579.9.
</P>
<P>
Analysts attributed the market inertia to the disclosure of
worse than expected interim reports of some listed companies.
</P>
<P>
The declining economic efficiency of blue chip stocks such as
Lujiazui dampened investors' confidence and led to sharply falling
prices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
