<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NCR Tags Chinese Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 18 (Xinhua) -- Computer giant NCR Corp. of the
United States will have a bigger market share in China with an
agreement signed with the People's Bank of China, "China Daily"
reported today.
</P>
<P>
"NCR would like to support China's drive to computerize the
financial industry with the world-latest technology and products,"
said Ken Chu, managing director of NCR (China) Ltd.
</P>
<P>
It will supply front-end computer equipment for the electronic
intra-settlement system of the People's Bank of China.
</P>
<P>
NCR will display a series of sophisticated banking solutions
including an unmanned bank, item-processing system, real-time
gross settlement, scalable-data warehousing, Internet banking and
call center and customer service information management systems
during the upcoming '97 Beijing International Financial Technology
and Equipment Fair.
</P>
<P>
Unmanned banks are considered the trend, featured by
convenience and low costs, for old-fashioned banks.
</P>
<P>
Ken predicts advanced technology in unmanned banks and data
warehousing will be embraced in China.
</P>
<P>
NCR recorded a turnover of 60 million US dollars in China last
year after it re-entered China's market in 1984.
</P>
<P>
The firm is the country's largest supplier of automatic teller
machines. Clients include almost all Chinese banks, financial
institutions and some major retailers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
