<HEADLINE> Quake Hits Indonesia's Kupang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 18 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.2 on
the Richter Scale hit the Eastern Region of Indonesia on Sunday,
Antara news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The quake was recorded in Sawu waters about 150 kilometers
southwest of Kupang in the Eastern Region at 11:53 in the morning.
</P>
<P>
The depth of the epicenter is within the normal limit, an
official from the Meteorology and Geophysics Service, Paulus
Winarso, was quoted as saying.  
</P>
</TEXT>
