<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Pakhalina Takes Three-meter Springboard Crown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Yulia Pakhalina of Russia won
the women's three-meter springboard event at the European Swimming
Championships in Seville, Spain on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 19-year-old Pakhalina performed an outstanding series of
five dives to upset her compatriot Vera Ilyna and finished first
with 567.30 points..
</P>
<P>
At the last European Championships two years ago, Pakhalina was
second to Ilyna in the event.
</P>
<P>
Pakhalina was the only diver in the day's competition to
achieve a high mark as over 70 points.
</P>
<P>
Ilyna, 23, who had won the one-meter springboard title on
Friday, had collected 524.28 points while Anna Lindberg of Sweden
won the bronze at 508.02 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
