<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kafelnikov Beats Rafter in Pilot Tennis Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov
of Russia collected his second title in three months by
outpowering Patrick Rafter of Australian 7-6 (7/4), 6-4 in the
final of the Pilot Pen International tournament in New Haven, the
United States on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The eighth seed Rafter fought off three break points in the
first set before forcing the tiebreaker. Kafelnikov won the
breaker at 7-4 and charged into the second set with an obviously
better hand.
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov lost his service for the only time when he took a
5-3 lead in the second set. But the World number six remained
calm and killed off the net-charging Australian 6-4 to win the
90-minute contest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
