<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seles Beats Huber to Win Canadian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Top-seeded Monica Seles won her
third Canadian Open in a row on Sunday with a 6-2, 6-4 victory
over eighth-seeded Anke Huber of Germany.
</P>
<P>
The victory was her eighth in a row over the eighth-ranked
Huber and it moved the 23-year-old Seles from third to second in
the rankings behind top-ranked Martina Hingis of Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Seles lost the opening game of the match before she quickly
picked up her game and won the set 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Huber, leading 4-3 in the second set, made five consecutive
unforced errors to allow Seles back into the set and won the
75-minute match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
