<HEADLINE> Large Foodstuff Processing Company Operational in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 18 (Xinhua) -- A 12-million-US dollar oil and
cereal processing company recently went operational in the bonded
zone of Zhangjiagang, a port city in east China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The Dongliang Industrial Co. was jointly funded by China
Cereal, Oil and Foodstuff Import and Export Corporation, the local
Zhangjiagang Bonded Zone Development Corporation, and other
investors from the United States, Singapore and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, some six factories catering to refiing of edible
oil, processing of animal feed and flour have been put into
production.
</P>
<P>
Its products have been established in the east China market and
exported to some southeast Asian countries as well as Hong Kong
and Macao regions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
