<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cameroon Clinches Last African Berth to World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOME, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Cameroon clinched Africa's last
place in next year's World Cup finals by fighting off home team
Zimbabwe 2-1 in Harare in a crucial African Zone World Cup Group
Four battle on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The triumph led Cameroon to come through with 14 points atop
the Group Four standings, followed by Angola with 10 points, who
tied 1-1 with Togo in Lome in another Group Four matchup.
</P>
<P>
Cameroon will make its fourth World Cup appearance next July in
France, the feat only shared by Morocco, who has already booked
their place in the finals.
</P>
<P>
Tunisia and Morocco, both of them marking the second time for
the international top flight football, as well as the newcomer
South Africa account for the remaining African finalists in France
next July. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
