<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bjorkman Wins Indianapolis Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Ninth seed Jonas Bjorkman of
Sweden won the 915,000 U.S. dollars RCA Championships by defeating
fifth seed Carlos Moya of Spain 2-0 in the final at Indianapolis,
the United States on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Bjorkman beat Moya 6-3, 7-6 (7-3) to win the 150,000 U.S.
dollars top prize. He broke Moya three times during the one-hour,
31-minute match.
</P>
<P>
This was the 25-year-old Bjorkman's second ATP Tour title this
year.
</P>
<P>
With the victory, the Swedish player has improved to 45-18 this
season. That moves him into second place in match wins this
season behind Michael Chang's 47.
</P>
<P>
Bjorkman also prevailed at the Bellsouth Open in Auckland in
January and was a finalist at Coral Springs in May. He will break
into the top 20 in next week's ATP Tour rankings for the first
time in his career.
</P>
<P>
This was also Bjorkman's first victory in three meetings with
Moya, including a five-set loss to the Spaniard in the fourth
round of this year's Australian Open.
</P>
<P>
For Moya, it was the fourth ATP Tour final of the year, but he
has lost all the four. He has been a finalist at Sydney and the
Australian Open on the hard surface, and Amsterdam two weeks ago
on clay.
</P>
<P>
Moya was seeking his third career ATP Tour title after winning
at Buenos Aires in 1995 and Umag, Croatia last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
