<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clintons Begin Vacation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 17 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
and his family Sunday headed off for a three-week vacation on
Martha's Vineyard, an island off the coast of Massachusetts.
</P>
<P>
En route, they stopped on Block Island, where Clinton said he
was anxious to see some of Block Island's pristine natural beauty
and encouraged residents to work to ensure the island remains that
way, news reports said.
</P>
<P>
This will be the third time the Clintons have spent a Summer
holiday on Martha's Vineyard. They plan to return to the White
House a few days after Labor Day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
