<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SFOR Acts to Prevent Bloodshed in Banja Luka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, August 17 (Xinhua)--Troops of the NATO-led
Stabilization Force (SFOR) on Sunday were deployed around the
headquarters of the public security center in Banja Luka to
prevent possible clashes between police factions in the Serb
territory.
</P>
<P>
A short statement by SFOR said the move was required by the
Office of the High Representative, the highest international
civilian authority in Bosnia, after the police headquarters were
taken over earlier in the day by special police loyal to
Republika Srpska President Biljana Plavsic.
</P>
<P>
Other sources said that the special police raided the
headquarters which had been controlled by the Pale-based
interior ministry and found bugging devices suspected of being
used to spy Plavsic by her opponents.
</P>
<P>
Over the past seven weeks, Plavsic and other RS government
leaders have been locked in an ever-deepening political crisis
over her decision to dismiss the interior minister and dissolve
the parliament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
